name: WorkerLocation
description: The WorkerLocation interface defines the absolute location of the script executed by the Worker. Such an object is initialized for each worker and is available via the WorkerGlobalScope.location property obtained by calling window.self.location.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.href
members.description: Is a DOMString containing the whole URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.protocol
members.description: Is a DOMString containing the protocol scheme of the URL of the script executed in the Worker, including the final ':'.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.host
members.description: Is a DOMString containing the host, that is the hostname, a ':', and the port of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.hostname
members.description: Is a DOMString containing the domain of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.origin
members.description: Returns a DOMString containing the canonical form of the origin of the specific location.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.port
members.description: Is a DOMString containing the port number of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.pathname
members.description: Is a DOMString containing an initial '/' followed by the path of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.search
members.description: Is a DOMString containing a '?' followed by the parameters of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.hash
members.description: Is a DOMString containing a '#' followed by the fragment identifier of the URL of the script executed in the Worker.

members.name: URLUtilsReadOnly.toString()
members.description: Returns a DOMString containing the whole URL of the script executed in the Worker. It is a synonym for URLUtilsReadOnly.href.
